7','2021-08-23 07:03:37','','index','','inherit','closed','closed','','index','','','2021-08-23 08:03:37','2021-08-23 07:03:37','',0,'http://opselcompliance.com/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/index.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(582,2,'2021-11-04 11:14:19','2021-11-04 11:14:19','<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"left\",\"id\":585,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full\"><img src=\"http://opselcompliance.com/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/iEoropol-Image-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-585\" /></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even when online purchasing has been made secure by implementing new technologies, such as Secure Customer Authentication or Two-Factor Authentication, cybercriminals still find ways to steal the hard-earned cash of online shoppers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>#SellSafe Awareness Campaign</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Europol, along with the Merchant Risk Council and participating countries, is launching the <strong>#SellSafe</strong> campaign yesterday. The aim of the campaign is to make e-commerce more secure by promoting safe online purchasing methods and by helping new merchants to open their first online shop without the risk of cyberattacks. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Europol is urging participating countries to promote the campaign through social media channels using the #SellSafe. Europol has provided a number of useful tips for E-Businesses and online shoppers. To read more on the useful tips to protect yourself and your business click <strong><a href=\"https://www.europol.europa.eu/newsroom/news/love-online-shopping-here%E2%80%99s-how-to-protect-yourself-against-online-scammers\">here</a></strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Europol launches campaign for fighting online fraud','','publish','open','open','','europol-launches-campaign